{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Resolved by landed commit 2271912cc 'fix(store): retry transient git object-DB failure on git add'. That commit routes the batched-import 'git add' through _git_add (src/rebar/_store/event_append.py:168-192), which retries up to 3x with backoff on the transient loose-object signature; the marker list includes the exact 'unable to create temporary file' string this test hit on macos-latest ('...: Invalid argument'), so it now self-heals instead of red-lighting CI. Commit ships a dedicated regression test (tests/interfaces/store/test_event_append_transient_retry.py) injecting the verbatim CI stderr. Verified NOT reproducible locally on darwin: test_benchmark_commit_count_is_ceil_per_pass -> 1 passed (54.6s). Closing as resolved. Residual (lower-probability): only 'git add' is retry-wrapped, not the subsequent 'git commit' loose-object write — filed as a separate follow-up if it ever recurs."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783718824196863001,"uuid":"9870ac80-6961-4ab4-a1e7-e3a4520e8d5f"}